Simulation

Type: object

Contains all information about Tidy3d simulation.

Example

sim = Simulation(
... size=(2.0, 2.0, 2.0),
... gridsize=(0.1, 0.1, 0.1),
... runtime=40e-11,
... structures=[
... Structure(
... geometry=Box(size=(1, 1, 1), center=(-1, 0, 0)),
... medium=Medium(permittivity=2.0),
... ),
... Structure(
... geometry=Box(size=(1, 1, 1), center=(0, 0, 0)),
... medium=Medium(permittivity=1.0, conductivity=3.0),
... ),
... Structure(geometry=Sphere(radius=1.4, center=(1.0, 0.0, 1.0)), medium=Medium()),
... Structure(
... geometry=Cylinder(radius=1.4, length=2.0, center=(1.0, 0.0, -1.0), axis=1),
... medium=Medium(),
... ),
... Structure(
... geometry=PolySlab(
... vertices=[(-1.5, -1.5), (-0.5, -1.5), (-0.5, -0.5)], slabbounds=[-1, 1]
... ),
... medium=Medium(permittivity=3.0),
... ),
... ],
... sources=[
... VolumeSource(
... size=(0, 0, 0),
... center=(0, 0.5, 0),
... polarization="Hx",
... sourcetime=GaussianPulse(
... freq0=2e14,
... fwidth=4e13,
... ),
... )
... ],
... monitors=[
... FieldMonitor(size=(0, 0, 0), center=(0, 0, 0), freqs=[1.5e14, 2e14], name='point'),
... FluxMonitor(size=(1, 1, 0), center=(0, 0, 0), freqs=[2e14, 2.5e14], name='flux'),
... ],
... symmetry=(0, 0, 0),
... pmllayers=(
... PML(numlayers=20),
... PML(num_layers=30),
... None,
... ),
... shutoff=1e-6,
... courant=0.8,
... subpixel=False,
... )

root grid_size
Type: array

If components are float, uniform grid size along x, y, and z. If components are array like, defines an array of nonuniform grid sizes centered at the simulation center . Note: if supplied sizes do not cover the simulation size, the first and last sizes are repeated to cover size.

root medium anyOf PoleResidue
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the pole-residue pair model.
The frequency-dependence of the complex-valued permittivity is described by:

.. math::

\epsilon(\omega) = \epsilon_\infty - \sum_i
\left[\frac{c_i}{j \omega + a_i} +
\frac{c_i^*}{j \omega + a_i^*}\right]

where :math:a_i and :math:c_i are in units of rad/s.

Parameters

epsinf : float = 1.0
Relative permittivity at infinite frequency (:math:\epsilon_\infty).
poles : List[Tuple[complex, complex]]
List of complex-valued (:math:a_i, c_i) poles for the model.
frequeuncyrange : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

poleres = PoleResidue(epsinf=2.0, poles=[(1+2j, 3+4j), (5+6j, 7+8j)])
eps = poleres.epsmodel(200e12)

root medium anyOf Sellmeier
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the Sellmeier model.
The frequency-dependence of the refractive index is described by:

.. math::

n(\lambda)^2 = 1 + \sum_i \frac{B_i \lambda^2}{\lambda^2 - C_i}

where :math:\lambda is in microns, :math:B_i is unitless and :math:C_i is in microns^2.

Parameters

coeffs : List[Tuple[float, float]]
List of Sellmeier (:math:B_i, C_i) coefficients.
frequeuncy_range : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

sellmeiermedium = Sellmeier(coeffs=[(1,2), (3,4)])
eps = sellmeiermedium.eps_model(200e12)

root medium anyOf Lorentz
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the Lorentz model.
The frequency-dependence of the complex-valued permittivity is described by:

.. math::
\epsilon(f) = \epsilon\infty + \sumi
\frac{\Delta\epsiloni fi^2}{fi^2 + 2jf\deltai - f^2}

where :math:f, f_i, \delta_i are in Hz.

Parameters

epsinf : float = 1.0
Relative permittivity at infinite frequency (:math:\epsilon_\infty).
coeffs : List[Tuple[float, float, float]]
List of (:math:\Delta\epsilon_i, f_i, \delta_i) values for model.
frequeuncyrange : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

lorentzmedium = Lorentz(epsinf=2.0, coeffs=[(1,2,3), (4,5,6)])
eps = lorentzmedium.epsmodel(200e12)

root structures Structure
Type: object

Defines a physical object that interacts with the electromagnetic fields.
A :class:Structure is a combination of a material property (:class:AbstractMedium)
and a :class:Geometry.

Example

box = Box(center=(0,0,1), size=(2, 2, 2))
glass = Medium(permittivity=3.9)
struct = Structure(geometry=box, medium=glass, name='glass_box')

No Additional Properties

root structures Structure medium

Defines the electromagnetic properties of the structure material.

  • Medium
  • AnisotropicMedium
  • PECMedium
  • PoleResidue
  • Sellmeier
  • Lorentz
  • Debye
  • Drude
root structures Structure medium anyOf Medium
Type: object

Dispersionless medium.

Example

dielectric = Medium(permittivity=4.0, name='mymedium')
eps = dielectric.epsmodel(200e12)

Same definition as Medium
root structures Structure medium anyOf AnisotropicMedium
Type: object

Diagonally anisotripic medium.

Note

Only diagonal anisotropy and non-dispersive components are currently supported.

Example

mediumxx = Medium(permittivity=4.0)
mediumyy = Medium(permittivity=4.1)
mediumzz = Medium(permittivity=3.9)
anisotropicdielectric = AnisotropicMedium(xx=mediumxx, yy=mediumyy, zz=medium_zz)

Same definition as AnisotropicMedium
root structures Structure medium anyOf PECMedium
Type: object

Perfect electrical conductor class.

Note

To avoid confusion from duplicate PECs, should import tidy3d.PEC instance directly.

Same definition as PECMedium
root structures Structure medium anyOf PoleResidue
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the pole-residue pair model.
The frequency-dependence of the complex-valued permittivity is described by:

.. math::

\epsilon(\omega) = \epsilon_\infty - \sum_i
\left[\frac{c_i}{j \omega + a_i} +
\frac{c_i^*}{j \omega + a_i^*}\right]

where :math:a_i and :math:c_i are in units of rad/s.

Parameters

epsinf : float = 1.0
Relative permittivity at infinite frequency (:math:\epsilon_\infty).
poles : List[Tuple[complex, complex]]
List of complex-valued (:math:a_i, c_i) poles for the model.
frequeuncyrange : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

poleres = PoleResidue(epsinf=2.0, poles=[(1+2j, 3+4j), (5+6j, 7+8j)])
eps = poleres.epsmodel(200e12)

Same definition as PoleResidue
root structures Structure medium anyOf Sellmeier
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the Sellmeier model.
The frequency-dependence of the refractive index is described by:

.. math::

n(\lambda)^2 = 1 + \sum_i \frac{B_i \lambda^2}{\lambda^2 - C_i}

where :math:\lambda is in microns, :math:B_i is unitless and :math:C_i is in microns^2.

Parameters

coeffs : List[Tuple[float, float]]
List of Sellmeier (:math:B_i, C_i) coefficients.
frequeuncy_range : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

sellmeiermedium = Sellmeier(coeffs=[(1,2), (3,4)])
eps = sellmeiermedium.eps_model(200e12)

Same definition as Sellmeier
root structures Structure medium anyOf Lorentz
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the Lorentz model.
The frequency-dependence of the complex-valued permittivity is described by:

.. math::
\epsilon(f) = \epsilon\infty + \sumi
frac{\Delta\epsiloni fi^2}{fi^2 + 2jf\deltai - f^2}

where :math:f, f_i, \delta_i are in Hz.

Parameters

epsinf : float = 1.0
Relative permittivity at infinite frequency (:math:\epsilon_\infty).
coeffs : List[Tuple[float, float, float]]
List of (:math:\Delta\epsilon_i, f_i, \delta_i) values for model.
frequeuncyrange : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

lorentzmedium = Lorentz(epsinf=2.0, coeffs=[(1,2,3), (4,5,6)])
eps = lorentzmedium.epsmodel(200e12)

Same definition as Lorentz
root structures Structure medium anyOf Debye
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the Debye model.
The frequency-dependence of the complex-valued permittivity is described by:

.. math::
\epsilon(f) = \epsilon\infty + \sumi
frac{\Delta\epsiloni}{1 + jf\taui}

where :math:f is in Hz, and :math:\tau_i is in seconds.

Parameters

epsinf : float = 1.0
Relative permittivity at infinite frequency (:math:\epsilon_\infty).
coeffs : List[Tuple[float, float, float]]
List of (:math:\Delta\epsilon_i, \tau_i) values for model.
frequeuncyrange : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

debyemedium = Debye(epsinf=2.0, coeffs=[(1,2),(3,4)])
eps = debyemedium.epsmodel(200e12)

Same definition as Debye
root structures Structure medium anyOf Drude
Type: object

A dispersive medium described by the Drude model.
The frequency-dependence of the complex-valued permittivity is described by:

.. math::
\epsilon(f) = \epsilon\infty - \sumi
frac{ fi^2}{f^2 - jf\deltai}

where :math:f, f_i, \delta_i are in Hz.

Parameters

epsinf : float = 1.0
Relative permittivity at infinite frequency (:math:\epsilon_\infty).
coeffs : List[Tuple[float, float]]
List of (:math:f_i, \delta_i) values for model.
frequeuncyrange : Tuple[float, float] = (-inf, inf)
Range of validity for the medium in Hz.
If simulation or plotting functions use frequency out of this range, a warning is thrown.
name : str = None
Optional name for the medium.

Example

drudemedium = Drude(epsinf=2.0, coeffs=[(1,2), (3,4)])
eps = drudemedium.epsmodel(200e12)

Same definition as Drude

root sources sources items anyOf PlaneWave pol_angle
Type: number Default: 0

Specifies the angle between the electric field polarization of the source and the plane defined by the normal axis and the propagation axis (rad). pol_angle=0 (default) specifies P polarization, while pol_angle=np.pi/2 specifies S polarization. At normal incidence when S and P are undefined, pol_angle=0 defines: - Ey polarization for propagation along x.- Ex polarization for propagation along y.- Ex polarization for propagation along z.

Parameters to feed to mode solver which determine modes measured by monitor.
root sources sources items anyOf ModeSource mode_spec allOf ModeSpec
Type: object

Stores specifications for the mode solver to find an electromagntic mode.
Note, the planar axes are found by popping the propagation axis from {x,y,z}.
For example, if propagation axis is y, the planar axes are ordered {x,z}.

Example

modespec = ModeSpec(nummodes=3, target_neff=1.5, symmetries=(1,-1))

No Additional Properties

root sources sources items anyOf ModeSource mode_spec allOf ModeSpec target_neff
Type: number

Guess for effective index of the mode.

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root sources sources items anyOf ModeSource mode_spec allOf ModeSpec symmetries
Type: array Default: [0, 0]

Symmetries to apply to mode solver for first two non-propagation axes. Values of (0, 1,-1) correspond to (none, even, odd) symmetries, respectvely.

root sources sources items anyOf GaussianBeam pol_angle
Type: number Default: 0

Specifies the angle between the electric field polarization of the source and the plane defined by the normal axis and the propagation axis (rad). pol_angle=0 (default) specifies P polarization, while pol_angle=np.pi/2 specifies S polarization. At normal incidence when S and P are undefined, pol_angle=0 defines: - Ey polarization for propagation along x.- Ex polarization for propagation along y.- Ex polarization for propagation along z.

Parameters to feed to mode solver which determine modes measured by monitor.
root monitors monitors items anyOf ModeMonitor mode_spec allOf ModeSpec
Type: object

Stores specifications for the mode solver to find an electromagntic mode.
Note, the planar axes are found by popping the propagation axis from {x,y,z}.
For example, if propagation axis is y, the planar axes are ordered {x,z}.

Example

modespec = ModeSpec(nummodes=3, target_neff=1.5, symmetries=(1,-1))

Same definition as ModeSpec

root symmetry
Type: array Default: [0, 0, 0]

Tuple of integers defining reflection symmetry across a plane bisecting the simulation domain normal to the x-, y-, and z-axis, respectvely. Each element can be '0' (no symmetry), '1' (even, i.e. 'PMC' symmetry) or '-1' (odd, i.e. 'PEC' symmetry). Note that the vectorial nature of the fields must be taken into account to correctly determine the symmetry value.

root shutoff
Type: number Default: 1e-05

Ratio of the instantaneous integrated E-field intensity to the maximum value at which the simulation will automatically terminate time stepping. Used to prevent extraneous run time of simulations with fully decayed fields. Set to '0' to disable this feature.

Value must be greater or equal to 0

root subpixel
Type: boolean Default: true

If 'True', uses subpixel averaging of the permittivity based on structure definition, resulting in much higher accuracy for a given grid size.

root courant
Type: number Default: 0.9

Courant stability factor, controls time step to spatial step ratio. Lower values lead to more stable simulations for dispersive materials, but result in longer simulation times.

Value must be strictly greater than 0.0 and lesser or equal to 1.0
